{{!--
  /freestyle/operators — standalone modifier vocabulary reference.

  Pure URL promotion of the modifier-reference content that also lives
  inside /freestyle/glossary §6. The same shared partial
  `freestyle-modifier-reference` renders the body on both surfaces.

  Zero new content; the dedicated URL exists purely to make the
  modifier vocabulary discoverable outside the glossary.
--}}
<div class="hero hero-sm">
  <div>
    {{#if navigation.breadcrumbs}}
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      {{#each navigation.breadcrumbs}}
        {{#if href}}<a href="{{href}}">{{label}}</a> <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span> {{else}}<span>{{label}}</span>{{/if}}
      {{/each}}
    </nav>
    {{/if}}
    <h1>{{page.title}}</h1>
    {{#if page.intro}}<p class="hero-subtitle">{{page.intro}}</p>{{/if}}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <section class="content-section">
    <p>
      Modifiers are the movement ideas that transform one trick into many
      &mdash; a spin, a duck, a paradox layered onto a base trick. Below: how
      each common modifier feels, then a structural reference for how they
      combine. To browse the tricks that use a given modifier, open the
      <a href="/freestyle/tricks?view=movement-system">By Movement System</a>
      view in the trick dictionary. For set systems as first-class objects
      (what is pixie / stepping / atomic as a system?), see the
      <a href="/freestyle/sets">Set Encyclopedia</a>.
    </p>

    {{> freestyle-modifier-reference}}
  </section>
</div>
